 By the universal property of the pullback, there is a unique
  map c\to  d commuting with the diagram which induces g, but such maps
  c\to  d are exactly maps \Sigma _f m\to  n in C/y. This shows the
  desired adjunction.

We define \Pi _f by pullback in C/y, which is inherited from
  C. In particular, on an object c\xrightarrow {m} x in C/x, we note
  first that there is a map of exponential objects
  \left [c\xrightarrow {m}x\xrightarrow {f}y^{(x\xrightarrow {f} y)}\right ]\to  \left [x\xrightarrow {f}   y^{(x\xrightarrow {f} y)}\right ] induced
  by post-composition with m:





